or pretzels,

16:16.943 --> 16:18.178
something to munch on?

16:18.245 --> 16:20.047
No, I think we're out.

16:20.113 --> 16:21.781
We're always out.

16:21.848 --> 16:22.882
My mama's house,

16:22.949 --> 16:24.217
there's always
plenty food to eat.

16:24.284 --> 16:25.585
Maybe you should
live with your mama.

16:25.652 --> 16:26.619
Don't be sarcastic.

16:26.686 --> 16:27.754
Don't be a nudge.

16:27.820 --> 16:28.955
Don't call me
that nudge thing.

16:29.022 --> 16:31.658
Come on. I'm Italian.
I like to eat.

16:31.724 --> 16:33.126
I'm Yugoslavian.

16:33.193 --> 16:34.727
I don't like to cook,
especially for nudges.

16:34.794 --> 16:36.663
Yeah, don't call me
a nudge.

16:36.729 --> 16:39.132
Nudge, nudge, nudge.

16:39.199 --> 16:41.034
Give me those shoes.

16:41.101 --> 16:42.769
You going out
again tonight?

16:42.835 --> 16:44.003
Hey, Rosalie, come on.

16:44.071 --> 16:45.638
What? I haven't
said anything.

16:45.705 --> 16:48.275
I work every day. All day.
Okay? Every day.

16:48.341 --> 16:52.345
At night, I like to relax,
go out, have fun, you know.

16:52.412 --> 16:53.813
I thought you were
staying home.

16:53.880 --> 16:56.449
What for?

16:56.516 --> 16:58.585
What for?

16:58.651 --> 17:00.420
I don't know.

17:00.487 --> 17:04.391
Who knows?

17:04.457 --> 17:06.925
Well, like what?

17:06.992 --> 17:10.530
Well, for one thing,
we've got paperwork.

17:10.597 --> 17:12.964
Paperwork?

17:13.031 --> 17:15.968
The monthly bills,
the insurance, the mortgage,

17:16.035 --> 17:17.104
the phone bill.

17:17.170 --> 17:18.771
I'm going out.

17:18.838 --> 17:21.441
* Miss Mary Mac, Mac, Mac

17:21.508 --> 17:23.643
* At the discotheque
Theque, theque *

17:23.710 --> 17:25.778
* I'm going to get her,
her, her

17:25.845 --> 17:29.382
* Down on
Her back, back, back... *

17:48.301 --> 17:49.336
Vodka, please.

18:01.981 --> 18:03.049
Mickey, that's on me.

18:03.116 --> 18:04.817
You got it, Joey.

18:04.884 --> 18:07.720
Joey Boca's my name.

18:07.787 --> 18:09.222
And you know what?

18:09.289 --> 18:10.890
I know something
about you.

18:10.957 --> 18:13.025
Yeah? What do you know
about me?

18:13.092 --> 18:15.595
I know you never been
in here before in your life.

18:15.662 --> 18:17.964
Really? How do you know?
Maybe I have.

18:18.030 --> 18:20.433
If you had, I would
have known about it.

18:20.500 --> 18:21.734
People would have
talked about it.

18:21.801 --> 18:24.271
Like, "Joey, you see

18:24.337 --> 18:26.206
"what was in here
the other night?

18:26.273 --> 18:27.274
My God, what a beauty."

18:27.340 --> 18:29.309
It's true.

18:29.376 --> 18:30.877
No, someone like you

18:30.943 --> 18:32.145
doesn't come
around that often.

18:32.212 --> 18:33.446
It's like
a national holiday.

18:33.513 --> 18:34.614
Know what I mean?

18:34.681 --> 18:36.716
You don't forget it.

18:42.855 --> 18:45.425
Listen,
I appreciate the drink,

18:45.492 --> 18:47.126
but I'm with someone.

18:47.194 --> 18:48.228
Someone very lucky.

18:48.295 --> 18:50.897
I wish I could be
that lucky.

18:50.963 --> 18:53.366
I look at you
and I say to myself,

18:53.433 --> 18:54.901
"My God, the man
who gets to walk

18:54.967 --> 18:57.704
"with this woman must feel
like a king on earth."

18:57.770 --> 19:00.940
Here's to you.

19:08.581 --> 19:10.883
I guess
I'd better get back.

19:10.950 --> 19:12.719
Show me your boyfriend.

19:12.785 --> 19:14.954
I want to see him
with my own eyes,

19:15.021 --> 19:17.424
so I can spend
the rest of my life

19:17.490 --> 19:19.726
wishing I was him.

19:22.662 --> 19:24.664
He's sitting
in the corner.

19:24.731 --> 19:25.765
Over there.

19:30.537 --> 19:32.872
Not the one
in the yellow shirt?

19:32.939 --> 19:34.106
Yeah, that's him.

19:34.173 --> 19:36.175
No.

19:36.243 --> 19:37.109
Yeah.

19:37.176 --> 19:38.110
No.

19:38.177 --> 19:40.146
Yeah, that's him.

19:40.213 --> 19:41.681
Why?

19:41.748 --> 19:46.919
You expect me to believe
that a beauty like you,

19:46.986 --> 19:49.922
a woman any man
would die to be with,

19:49.989 --> 19:53.260
is throwing herself away
on someone like that?

19:53.326 --> 19:55.728
You could have anyone. Anyone.

19:55.795 --> 19:59.198
Why would you take him?

19:59.266 --> 20:00.900
He's not my boyfriend
or anything.

20:00.967 --> 20:03.836
I just came here
with him.

20:03.903 --> 20:07.139
I'm not in love with him
or anything.

20:07.206 --> 20:14.414
Of course not.
How could you be?

20:14.481 --> 20:20.052
[HALL & OATES'
"YOU MAKE MY DREAMS" PLAYS]

21:01.294 --> 21:03.496
[MOANING]

21:14.674 --> 21:15.975
[GROWLS]

21:20.880 --> 21:24.016
[BARKS]

21:24.083 --> 21:26.619
Is he going
to watch or what?

21:26.686 --> 21:28.087
Does it bother you?

21:28.154 --> 21:30.423
Well, I'm Italian,
you know.

21:30.490 --> 21:32.659
I can't make love
to a woman

21:32.725 --> 21:34.093
with a German shepherd
in the room.

21:34.160 --> 21:35.728
It's awkward for him.

21:35.795 --> 21:37.564
You can't?

21:45.104 --> 21:46.506
[BARKS]

21:48.641 --> 21:49.842
Excuse me.

21:49.909 --> 21:51.310
Here you go.

21:51.378 --> 21:53.580
Attaboy.

21:55.915 --> 21:58.518
Auf Wiedersehen, Heinz.

22:03.956 --> 22:05.392
I can't figure it out.

22:05.458 --> 22:07.193
A young, good-looking
guy like you,

22:07.259 --> 22:10.329
how come you're always
hanging out with Rosalie?

22:10.397 --> 22:12.965
I enjoy her company.

22:13.032 --> 22:15.201
You're not moving in
on my wife?

22:15.267 --> 22:19.171
No, of course not.
What are you, kidding?

22:19.238 --> 22:20.507
That's ludicrous.

22:20.573 --> 22:22.375
You're being ridiculous.

22:22.442 --> 22:24.076
What's ridiculous?

22:24.143 --> 22:25.211
There's nobody
like Rosalie.

22:25.277 --> 22:26.245
Right.

22:26.312 --> 22:27.279
She's the best.

22:27.346 --> 22:28.615
Exactly.

22:28.681 --> 22:29.382
I can't believe
you're saying that.

22:29.449 --> 22:32.652
Why not? She's my wife.

22:32.719 --> 22:36.088
Yeah, I know.
I look at other women.

22:36.155 --> 22:38.791
Okay. So what?
That's only natural.

22:38.858 --> 22:40.059
I'm a human man.

22:40.126 --> 22:41.694
It don't hurt Rosalie.

22:41.761 --> 22:43.463
How can you say that?

22:43.530 --> 22:45.765
Even if she knows,
she don't care.

22:45.832 --> 22:47.133
That's how she is.

22:47.199 --> 22:48.334
Oh yeah?

22:48.401 --> 22:50.302
Well, that's
pure projection.

22:50.369 --> 22:51.571
Pure what?

22:51.638 --> 22:53.072
Projection.

22:53.139 --> 22:55.908
It's projection,
what you want to think.

22:55.975 --> 22:57.343
What I want to think?

22:57.410 --> 22:59.011
Yeah, it makes you
feel good

22:59.078 --> 23:01.581
to think
that she's happy.

23:01.648 --> 23:03.483
Yeah!

23:03.550 --> 23:07.219
As long as she's happy,
I'm happy.

23:07.286 --> 23:09.656
I'm glad we understand
each other.

23:09.722 --> 23:13.092
Well, me too.

23:13.159 --> 23:15.828
I hear Spino took off
to Bellingham?

23:15.895 --> 23:17.630
Yeah.

23:17.697 --> 23:18.698
Yeah?

23:18.765 --> 23:19.732
Got to go, man.

23:19.799 --> 23:21.333
Okay, take it easy, Billy.

23:28.541 --> 23:30.677
How do you know
these weird people?

23:30.743 --> 23:34.213
That guy was in prison
with my brother.

23:34.280 --> 23:35.815
My first boyfriend
had a Harley.

23:35.882 --> 23:37.950
Rocco Jacobs.

23:40.086 --> 23:43.990
What a piece of work he was.

23:44.056 --> 23:45.592
We used to go fast.

23:45.658 --> 23:47.760
Maybe I should get a bike.

23:47.827 --> 23:53.132
Sure. Why not?
Drives the girls crazy.

23:53.199 --> 23:54.834
I was wild back then.

23:54.901 --> 23:57.704
So what happened to Rocco?

23:57.770 --> 23:59.171
Joey Boca happened.

23:59.238 --> 24:01.007
He said, "Hey, I'm Joey.
You want to go out?

24:01.073 --> 24:03.109
What are you doing
with that jerk?"

24:05.878 --> 24:08.615
As soon as I saw Joey,
I knew he was the one.

24:08.681 --> 24:09.916
So fast?

24:09.982 --> 24:11.117
Sure, fast.

24:11.183 --> 24:12.619
I do what I feel.

24:12.685 --> 24:14.186
Then you must have felt
suicidal.

24:14.253 --> 24:18.357
Shut up.

24:18.424 --> 24:22.128
Some day, you're going to find
a wonderful woman,

24:22.194 --> 24:24.296
and you'll drive her crazy
with this big motorcycle.

24:24.363 --> 24:26.232
I found myself
a wonderful woman,

24:26.298 --> 24:27.333
but she's married.

24:27.399 --> 24:30.970
Devo, you're good for my ego.

24:31.037 --> 24:32.705
You've got to meet somebody
your own age.

24:32.772 --> 24:34.240
Why?

24:34.306 --> 24:36.275
Your heart doesn't know
how old you are.

24:36.342 --> 24:37.610
Hi. Is Joey around?

24:37.677 --> 24:39.145
No, he's not.

24:39.211 --> 24:41.380
I'm his wife.
Can I help you?

24:41.447 --> 24:44.751
Oh...

24:44.817 --> 24:46.686
I met him at a bowling alley,

24:46.753 --> 24:48.988
and he told me he had
some apartments to rent.

24:49.055 --> 24:50.022
He's up there right now.

24:50.089 --> 24:51.824
Fixing the pipes.

24:51.891 --> 24:53.560
This is my friend, Devo.

24:53.626 --> 24:55.194
What is your name?

24:55.261 --> 24:56.663
Bridget.

24:56.729 --> 24:57.697
Bridget.

24:57.764 --> 24:58.698
Bridget, meet Devo.

24:58.765 --> 24:59.932
Hi.

24:59.999 --> 25:01.200
Hello.

25:01.267 --> 25:05.271
Come on. I'll take you up.

25:09.809 --> 25:12.779
I think it's time I was
moving out of my house.

25:12.845 --> 25:15.047
I was about your age
when I moved out.

25:15.114 --> 25:16.649
I got married to Joey.

25:16.716 --> 25:17.750
Now my mother
lives with us.

25:17.817 --> 25:19.018
That must be fun.

25:19.085 --> 25:20.319
It's okay.

25:20.386 --> 25:21.854
Oh, here's Joey now.

25:21.921 --> 25:26.525
Bridget, how you doing?
What are you doing here?

25:26.593 --> 25:29.562
She wants to look at
one of the apartments, baby.

25:29.629 --> 25:30.462
Today?

25:30.529 --> 25:31.898
Do you have any vacancies?

25:31.964 --> 25:35.101
We might have one
coming up next month.

25:35.167 --> 25:37.269
Might as well take a look
while she's here.

25:37.336 --> 25:39.672
Yeah, yeah.

25:39.739 --> 25:40.773
No.

25:40.840 --> 25:42.141
No, it's--

25:42.208 --> 25:44.110
It's not a good time.

25:44.176 --> 25:45.645
Maybe tomorrow.
How's that?

25:45.712 --> 25:47.580
Sure. Tomorrow.

25:47.647 --> 25:49.415
Well, it was nice to meet you,
Mrs. Boca.

25:49.481 --> 25:51.283
Rosalie.

25:51.350 --> 25:52.551
Rosalie.

25:52.619 --> 25:53.552
Bye.

25:53.620 --> 25:54.721
Bye-bye, now.

25:54.787 --> 25:56.255
Bye-bye.

25:56.956 --> 25:58.024
She came all this way.

25:58.090 --> 25:59.926
You couldn't
show her today?

25:59.992 --> 26:02.361
No, no. I've got a lot to do.
I'm not Superman.

26:02.428 --> 26:06.398
Hey, Joey!

26:06.465 --> 26:07.566
You forgot this.

26:08.267 --> 26:11.003
Thanks.

26:12.939 --> 26:15.241
I don't like
that Dewey Brown.

26:15.307 --> 26:17.509
Why not?
She's a nice girl.

26:17.576 --> 26:18.845
She's got eyes
for you, Joey.

26:18.911 --> 26:19.912
What?

26:19.979 --> 26:21.080
I can see that.

26:21.147 --> 26:22.715
Come on.
She's only a kid.

26:22.782 --> 26:26.152
She's very pretty.
You think she's pretty?

26:26.218 --> 26:27.419
She's pretty.

26:27.486 --> 26:28.855
She's got
a beautiful body too.

26:28.921 --> 26:30.156
So what?
What do I care?

26:30.222 --> 26:32.158
You're the best wife
in the world.

26:32.224 --> 26:34.026
What more could I want?

26:37.630 --> 26:39.065
You work too hard.

26:39.131 --> 26:40.867
You should get a plumber.

26:40.933 --> 26:43.736
I can't afford that,
and you know it.

26:43.803 --> 26:46.338
I can never get you
to fix anything at home.

26:46.405 --> 26:47.874
Your mother
fixes everything.

26:47.940 --> 26:51.010
Grandma Mechanic:
half-woman, half-wrench.

26:51.077 --> 26:54.346
So this goes right here. See?

26:54.413 --> 26:56.749
Holds it together.

26:56.816 --> 26:59.719
This is a restaurant,
not a garage.

26:59.786 --> 27:01.553
Grandma Nadja
can fix anything.

27:01.620 --> 27:03.856
She fixed
Mommy's car yesterday.

27:03.923 --> 27:05.324
Alternator was shot.

27:05.391 --> 27:09.662
It's not natural, a woman
doing this kind of work.

27:09.729 --> 27:12.131
You know, people get paid
$20, $30 an hour

27:12.198 --> 27:13.700
for this kind of work.

27:13.766 --> 27:16.002
You get free room and board.
What more do you want?

27:16.068 --> 27:18.037
Don't talk to Mama that way!

27:18.104 --> 27:20.106
She belongs in an
old-age home.

27:20.172 --> 27:23.710
[SPEAKS SERBIAN]

27:23.776 --> 27:25.277
What did she say?

27:25.344 --> 27:26.879
Don't listen to him, okay?

27:26.946 --> 27:28.614
[SPEAKS SERBIAN]

27:30.016 --> 27:32.218
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

27:35.922 --> 27:37.556
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

27:37.623 --> 27:40.326
[SPEAKS SERBIAN]

27:40.392 --> 27:43.763
[ARGUING IN SERBIAN
AND ITALIAN]

27:49.568 --> 27:51.537
I'll come back later.

27:57.443 --> 27:58.610
What's the matter, Dom?

27:58.677 --> 27:59.712
What happened?

27:59.779 --> 28:00.679
I hurt my finger.

28:00.747 --> 28:02.048
Let me see.

28:02.114 --> 28:03.382
We can fix that.

28:03.449 --> 28:05.417
Here. No problem.

28:05.484 --> 28:06.452
We'll fix it right up.

28:06.518 --> 28:07.754
Now put that
in your mouth.

28:07.820 --> 28:08.955
How's that?

28:09.021 --> 28:10.957
Better? Yeah?

28:11.023 --> 28:13.559
Good. That's my boy.

28:13.625 --> 28:14.827
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

28:14.894 --> 28:16.963
[SPEAKS SERBIAN]

28:17.029 --> 28:19.431
Can we eat?

28:22.634 --> 28:24.670
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

28:32.278 --> 28:33.312
I'm returning these.

28:33.379 --> 28:35.581
Okay. Thanks.

28:51.663 --> 28:54.433
JOEY: What am I doing
in a library?

28:56.302 --> 28:58.504
What's that perfume?
You smell so good.

28:59.238 --> 29:00.406
DONNA JOY:
Joey.

29:00.472 --> 29:01.540
What?

29:01.607 --> 29:03.675
Not here. They're
going to throw us out.

29:03.742 --> 29:06.212
Good.

29:06.278 --> 29:08.080
Get your book,
and let's get out of here.

29:08.147 --> 29:10.749
Where are we
going to go?

29:10.817 --> 29:13.119
I say we go
to your place,

29:13.185 --> 29:14.186
have a good time.

29:14.253 --> 29:16.322
What about your wife?

29:16.388 --> 29:19.525
No, she can't come.

29:21.861 --> 29:23.095
All set? Come on.

29:23.162 --> 29:25.531
I've got to
get back to work soon.

29:51.090 --> 29:52.491
Mrs. Boca?

29:52.558 --> 29:55.027
Hi, Millie. Hi.

29:55.094 --> 29:56.428
You okay?

29:56.495 --> 29:57.429
Did somebody mug you?

29:57.496 --> 30:01.433
I'm fine, sweetie.

30:01.500 --> 30:04.070
I...

30:04.136 --> 30:07.673
I lost something,
but it's okay.

30:07.739 --> 30:10.009
You go ahead, guys.
I'll be all right.

30:10.076 --> 30:12.278
Could we help you
look for it?

30:12.344 --> 30:17.016
I'll find it.

30:17.083 --> 30:17.917
Okay.

30:17.984 --> 30:19.585
Come on.

30:45.912 --> 30:49.781
Fool. Stupid fool!

31:56.582 --> 31:58.985
Divorce him? No, never.
Why should I?

31:59.051 --> 32:00.987
So he can move in
with some other woman?

32:01.053 --> 32:02.088
I'd rather see him dead first.

32:02.154 --> 32:05.191
Good. He deserves to die.

32:05.257 --> 32:09.295
Leaves dirty towels
everywhere. He's a mess.

32:09.361 --> 32:12.965
I hate him, Mama.

32:13.032 --> 32:15.434
All these years,
what a fool I am.

32:15.501 --> 32:17.936
Devo tried
to warn me too.

32:18.004 --> 32:24.043
The sooner he's dead,
the sooner you begin to live.

32:24.110 --> 32:27.079
I know someone
who needs money.

32:27.146 --> 32:28.680
He'd do it.

32:28.747 --> 32:31.583
He's a good boy,
very nice.

32:31.650 --> 32:33.552
How do you know
these sort of people?

32:33.619 --> 32:35.054
I've got
a lot of friends.

32:35.121 --> 32:36.655
You know that.

32:36.722 --> 32:38.357
Killers?

32:38.424 --> 32:40.192
Not real killers, no.

32:40.259 --> 32:42.561
They only do it
for money.

32:46.132 --> 32:47.633
What if we get caught?

32:47.699 --> 32:49.435
Oh, Rosalie, please.

32:49.501 --> 32:52.204
In America, people kill
each other left and right.

32:52.271 --> 32:54.006
It's like national pastime.

32:54.073 --> 32:56.142
Nobody gets caught.

32:58.010 --> 32:59.311
I don't know.

32:59.378 --> 33:01.480
I just haven't done
this kind of thing

33:01.547 --> 33:03.149
in a long time.

33:03.215 --> 33:05.251
Well, it comes
back easy.

33:05.317 --> 33:06.685
When was last time?

33:06.752 --> 33:09.355
It was a long time ago.
I don't remember exactly.

33:09.421 --> 33:11.957
Well, you'll do it for me.

33:12.024 --> 33:13.459
Okay.

33:13.525 --> 33:15.327
In honor of your friendship
with my grandmother,

33:15.394 --> 33:18.597
I guarantee I'll take
this guy out.

33:18.664 --> 33:20.899
Okay. You're very good boy.

33:20.966 --> 33:23.535
So many young people today,
they have no respect.

33:23.602 --> 33:25.737
I think
it's because of TV,

33:25.804 --> 33:27.173
so much sex and violence.

33:27.239 --> 33:29.775
Yeah, who can figure what
this world's coming to?

33:56.168 --> 33:57.969
Wrong house.

34:03.975 --> 34:06.978
Son of a bitch, bastard!

34:13.485 --> 34:15.721
[GROANS]

34:15.786 --> 34:17.123
Rosalie!

34:17.188 --> 34:20.659
It was unbelievable.
It was by this much.

34:20.726 --> 34:22.494
Come on in. Sit down here.

34:22.561 --> 34:24.295
I appreciate your
coming over so quick.

34:24.362 --> 34:26.165
Well, it's okay.

34:26.232 --> 34:27.565
Ever hear of it?

34:27.632 --> 34:29.201
Trying to hit me
with a baseball bat?

34:29.268 --> 34:31.237
My God,
it's unbelievable.

34:31.303 --> 34:33.071
Rosalie,
what are you doing?

34:33.139 --> 34:35.005
Get Detective Schooner
a cup of coffee.

34:35.072 --> 34:36.842
No. I'm okay, Rosalie.
Thank you.

34:36.908 --> 34:39.245
No, she'll make you coffee
in five minutes.

34:39.311 --> 34:41.513
Thanks, Joey.
I'm trying to give it up.

34:41.580 --> 34:42.914
No, come on, please--

34:42.981 --> 34:47.119
You give up coffee?
Never heard of that.

34:47.186 --> 34:49.054
Makes me jumpy.

34:49.121 --> 34:52.391
Jumpy?

34:52.458 --> 34:55.226
Rosalie, how about
some bacon and eggs for Larry?

34:55.293 --> 34:56.828
He works hard.

34:56.895 --> 35:01.567
Nothing for me, thank you.
Rosalie, please sit down.

35:01.633 --> 35:04.436
I didn't come here
for breakfast, Joey.

35:04.503 --> 35:07.673
Okay. From the beginning.

35:07.739 --> 35:11.577
Sure, from the beginning.
Okay.

35:11.643 --> 35:13.979
Some maniac
in an Abraham Lincoln mask

35:14.045 --> 35:16.582
tries to brain me
with a baseball bat.

35:16.648 --> 35:18.083
That's the whole story.

35:18.150 --> 35:21.320
Yeah, could you see
what he looked like?

35:21.387 --> 35:24.089
Yeah, he looked like

35:24.156 --> 35:27.593
Abraham Lincoln
coming up to bat.

35:27.659 --> 35:30.696
What kind of way
is that to kill somebody?

35:30.762 --> 35:32.097
A baseball bat?

35:32.164 --> 35:34.600
Now I know why you think
murder's the national pastime.

35:34.666 --> 35:37.035
Baseball bat is much
cheaper than gun.

35:37.102 --> 35:39.305
Abraham Lincoln is cheaper
than George Washington?

35:39.371 --> 35:40.572
I don't know him.

35:56.021 --> 35:57.823
JOEY: Rosalie,
where are you?

35:57.889 --> 35:59.725
Now what
are we going to do?

35:59.791 --> 36:01.827
This time, I take care
of everything.

36:01.893 --> 36:03.295
We'll talk tomorrow.

36:03.362 --> 36:05.130
This is wrong.
It's wrong.

36:05.197 --> 36:07.899
You leave it to me.
I do it myself.

36:07.966 --> 36:09.501
No! Don't do
anything.

36:09.568 --> 36:10.902
We'll talk tomorrow.

36:15.241 --> 36:16.375
What are you doing out here?

36:16.442 --> 36:18.844
What?

36:18.910 --> 36:21.179
What are you doing?

36:21.247 --> 36:22.080
Just getting some air.

36:22.147 --> 36:23.582
Come on.

36:23.649 --> 36:25.451
There's a maniac loose
in the neighborhood.

36:25.517 --> 36:26.852
Get in the house.

36:26.918 --> 36:28.520
What? Is everybody crazy?

36:36.695 --> 36:38.364
[CLICK]

36:38.430 --> 36:40.198
Son of a bitch!

36:40.266 --> 36:42.634
All right, Mr. Abraham
Lincoln, son of a bitch,
bastard!

36:42.701 --> 36:44.870
Now what are you
going to do, huh?

36:44.936 --> 36:45.904
Yeah--

36:45.971 --> 36:46.905
What are you doing?

36:46.972 --> 36:49.341
Nothing. I've got my gun.

36:49.408 --> 36:50.942
What do you want
a gun for?

36:51.009 --> 36:53.545
I figure that guy in the mask
is trying to rob me.

36:53.612 --> 36:54.846
Business is good.

36:54.913 --> 36:57.449
People think I carry
a lot of cash around.

36:57.516 --> 36:59.551
I don't like
having a gun in the house

36:59.618 --> 37:01.152
with the children.

37:46.465 --> 37:51.470
* Don't forget
You are my darling *

37:51.537 --> 37:54.906
* Don't forget to be... *

38:13.058 --> 38:14.626
Rosalie,
come on, if you're coming.

38:16.462 --> 38:17.463
Joey, wait up.

38:17.529 --> 38:18.964
I'm not a track star.

38:20.065 --> 38:21.367
What's the matter?

38:21.433 --> 38:23.001
Look what he did
to this bush.

38:23.068 --> 38:24.202
Come on. Let's go.

38:30.842 --> 38:32.210
No! No, stop!

38:32.277 --> 38:35.481
Wait! Wait.
No, wait.

38:35.547 --> 38:36.715
What's wrong?

38:36.782 --> 38:38.350
What are you doing?

38:38.417 --> 38:39.951
Going to work.

38:40.018 --> 38:41.152
No, wait.

38:41.219 --> 38:42.621
What's the matter
with you?

38:42.688 --> 38:44.423
You never
go to work together.

38:44.490 --> 38:46.324
So today,
we go together.

38:46.392 --> 38:47.526
I didn't like the way

38:47.593 --> 38:49.495
my car sounded
this morning,

38:49.561 --> 38:50.596
so would you look at it?

38:50.662 --> 38:52.598
It's very bad luck

38:52.664 --> 38:55.767
for man and woman to go
together in car on Wednesday,

38:55.834 --> 38:56.902
when it's raining.

38:56.968 --> 38:58.537
It's raining. So what?

38:58.604 --> 39:00.171
It's wet.

39:00.238 --> 39:02.641
Rain is always wet.

39:02.708 --> 39:03.675
The streets are wet.

39:03.742 --> 39:04.776
Mama Nadja,
what are you doing?

39:04.843 --> 39:06.044
What's the matter with you?

39:06.111 --> 39:07.145
What the hell's
wrong with you?

39:07.212 --> 39:08.480
It's Wednesday.

39:08.547 --> 39:11.282
Do you mind?
We've got to go to work.

39:11.349 --> 39:14.853
Traffic is bad
on Wednesdays,

39:14.920 --> 39:16.321
especially when
streets are wet.

39:16.388 --> 39:17.823
You want me to stay home
because of traffic?

39:17.889 --> 39:20.392
I want Rosalie to stay home

39:20.459 --> 39:23.161
and help me with
the housecleaning.

39:23.228 --> 39:26.398
Housecleaning?

39:26.465 --> 39:27.466
I've got work to do.

39:27.533 --> 39:29.200
No!

39:29.267 --> 39:30.769
[ENGINE RUNNING SMOOTHLY]

39:36.207 --> 39:37.242
What's the matter with
you two?

39:45.283 --> 39:46.518
Why didn't you tell me

39:46.585 --> 39:48.086
you were going to
blow up the car?

39:48.153 --> 39:50.121
I thought it would be
a nice surprise for you.

39:50.188 --> 39:53.592
Mama, we're not talking about
a birthday party.

39:53.659 --> 39:55.994
We're supposed
to be killing him, not me.

39:56.061 --> 39:59.164
I don't know
what goes wrong.

39:59.230 --> 40:01.332
I run a wire
from distributor cap

40:01.399 --> 40:03.935
to spark plug
in gas tank.

40:04.002 --> 40:06.104
I figure when
he starts car, boom!

40:06.171 --> 40:07.272
Whole thing goes up.

40:07.338 --> 40:09.140
Bye-bye, Joey.

40:09.207 --> 40:11.142
Joey shouldn't
die that way.

40:11.209 --> 40:13.011
That's a terrible way
to die.

40:13.078 --> 40:14.245
Well, how should he die?

40:14.312 --> 40:17.749
I don't know,
but something a little more...

40:17.816 --> 40:20.218
Nicer?

40:20.285 --> 40:23.789
I'll think about it.

40:23.855 --> 40:25.223
He's still my husband.

40:25.290 --> 40:28.193
You said yourself you
hate him.

40:28.259 --> 40:30.762
When I think of
all the women he's been with--

40:30.829 --> 40:31.863
Oh, God, Mama!

40:31.930 --> 40:32.831
He cheats on you

40:32.898 --> 40:35.000
and makes
a fool of you.

40:35.066 --> 40:36.367
I know. I know.

40:36.434 --> 40:39.070
Rosalie, please,
if you don't kill him,

40:39.137 --> 40:40.238
kill yourself.

40:40.305 --> 40:42.207
I'm sure that
can be arranged.

40:42.273 --> 40:44.175
I see the code
specifically states--

40:45.877 --> 40:49.481
Stand fast in the ranks!

40:49.548 --> 40:51.382
You speak to me
of code?

40:51.449 --> 40:54.085
What code?

40:54.152 --> 40:57.756
A coward's code.

40:57.823 --> 41:01.192
What do you know of
the Soldier's Code?

41:01.259 --> 41:03.394
A lot of pepper.

41:08.099 --> 41:10.268
Some nice oregano.

41:10.335 --> 41:12.403
And a little basil.

41:17.442 --> 41:19.477
A lot of sleeping pills.

41:22.013 --> 41:24.215
You sure he won't
come in here?

41:24.282 --> 41:25.917
Joey? Not a chance.

41:25.984 --> 41:29.888
He expects to be waited on
hand and foot.

41:29.955 --> 41:31.757
Mama, don't taste it.

41:31.823 --> 41:33.424
Needs more pepper.

41:33.491 --> 41:36.895
Make it spicy.

41:36.962 --> 41:38.664
A little salt.

41:38.730 --> 41:40.932
And a splash of wine.

41:44.736 --> 41:46.805
And a lot
of sleeping pills.

41:49.474 --> 41:51.042
How much did you
put in so far?

41:51.109 --> 41:52.410
Two whole bottles.

41:52.477 --> 41:53.679
What?

41:53.745 --> 41:55.080
Should be enough
to kill anyone.

41:55.146 --> 41:56.314
Even Joey.

41:58.216 --> 42:00.218
He's going to do it.

42:00.285 --> 42:02.788
Believe me,
he's really going to do it.

42:02.854 --> 42:04.455
Here you go.

42:06.992 --> 42:09.394
I warn you,
Colonel Saito.

42:09.460 --> 42:10.996
Where are the kids?

42:11.062 --> 42:13.031
They're at Aunt Lucy's
for the weekend.

42:17.102 --> 42:20.238
Make sure
he eats it.

42:24.275 --> 42:25.644
What are you looking at?

42:25.711 --> 42:27.713
How's your spaghetti?

42:27.779 --> 42:30.448
Okay.

42:30.515 --> 42:33.018
There's plenty more.

42:40.859 --> 42:44.162
It's the best spaghetti
ever, Rosalie.

42:44.229 --> 42:49.500
See, nice and spicy,
just like my mother's.

42:52.403 --> 42:54.505
That's okay.

43:00.646 --> 43:02.247
Too bad the kids
are at Aunt Lucy's.

43:02.313 --> 43:04.883
They're missing
a great meal.

43:04.950 --> 43:07.853
[WHISTLING]

43:17.663 --> 43:19.064
One more helping.

43:19.130 --> 43:22.033
And bring me
another beer.

43:24.302 --> 43:27.038
What's the matter?
You're not hungry?

43:47.258 --> 43:48.426
I don't feel so good.

43:48.493 --> 43:52.998
No?

43:53.064 --> 43:54.733
A little stomachache.

43:54.800 --> 43:56.434
Is that all?

43:56.501 --> 43:58.169
What do you mean,
"Is that all?"

43:58.236 --> 44:00.105
What do you
want me to have?

44:00.171 --> 44:01.940
Maybe you should
take something.

44:02.007 --> 44:03.508
Like what?

44:03.574 --> 44:06.644
How about some more
spaghetti?

44:06.712 --> 44:08.079
Spaghetti?

44:08.146 --> 44:09.815
Settles the stomach.

44:09.881 --> 44:12.250
I'll go get some.

44:15.620 --> 44:16.855
I don't know.

44:16.922 --> 44:18.456
Maybe I didn't
give him enough.

44:18.523 --> 44:20.926
But he had
three whole bowls.

44:20.992 --> 44:22.160
What an ox.

44:22.227 --> 44:24.229
Well, Joey
is not a normal man.

44:24.295 --> 44:25.596
You know how he is.

44:25.663 --> 44:28.800
Works 14,
15 hours a day,

44:28.867 --> 44:30.568
seven days a week,

44:30.635 --> 44:34.139
never sleeps more than
two or three hours a night.

44:34.205 --> 44:37.175
Out with a different woman
every night.

44:37.242 --> 44:39.177
Rosalie...

44:39.244 --> 44:43.481
He eats anything he wants,
never gains any weight.

44:43.548 --> 44:45.350
He's not human.

44:45.416 --> 44:48.119
It's like
some kind of animal.

44:48.186 --> 44:49.554
We're dealing
with a machine.

44:49.620 --> 44:50.889
Rosalie!
What?

44:50.956 --> 44:54.826
I feel better now.

44:54.893 --> 44:59.464
I had a good crap.
That's all I needed.

44:59.530 --> 45:04.302
What a beautiful night!

45:10.942 --> 45:13.378
See?

45:13.444 --> 45:15.046
[SINGS IN ITALIAN]

45:15.113 --> 45:21.920
* Means don't forget
You are my darlings *

45:21.987 --> 45:26.224
Come on.
You're not singing.

45:26.291 --> 45:32.330
* Don't forget to be
All you mean to me... *

45:39.604 --> 45:42.140
* My love is like a star

45:42.207 --> 45:46.144
* My darling

45:46.211 --> 45:48.046
[JOEY FARTS]

45:48.113 --> 45:55.086
* Shining bright and clear
Just because you're here *

45:55.153 --> 45:58.957
* Please do not forget...

45:59.024 --> 46:05.030
* Why the hell
Are you leaving? *

46:17.075 --> 46:19.777
Come on, ladies. Let's go.

46:19.845 --> 46:22.881
Monopoly.

46:26.985 --> 46:30.922
ANNOUNCER: Whoa, the Wild Hare
is feeling his oats tonight.

46:30.989 --> 46:32.257
A close call.

46:32.323 --> 46:33.691
That's what
it looks like,

46:33.758 --> 46:35.226
but we'll wait
for the measurement.

46:35.293 --> 46:36.294
No more.

46:36.361 --> 46:39.330
You finish it.

46:39.397 --> 46:42.167
A starting-line launch
gave him the advantage.

46:42.233 --> 46:45.336
Completely airborne
over the cars,

46:45.403 --> 46:47.839
but inches behind
Barefoot, the winner.

46:47.906 --> 46:50.475
[**]

46:50.541 --> 46:54.412
Joey? Joey?

47:00.651 --> 47:03.688
[SNORING]

47:04.822 --> 47:05.790
What are you doing?

47:05.857 --> 47:06.757
We shoot him.

47:06.824 --> 47:08.126
No! No.

47:08.193 --> 47:09.995
But we have to.
We can't go back now.

47:10.061 --> 47:11.229
No, we've gone too far.

47:11.296 --> 47:14.632
If we take him
to the hospital,

47:14.699 --> 47:17.635
they find him
full of dreamies.

47:17.702 --> 47:20.005
They'll know
we tried to kill him.

47:20.071 --> 47:21.806
We have no choice.

47:21.873 --> 47:23.708
We can't do that.

47:23.774 --> 47:25.143
We can't shoot him, Mama.

47:25.210 --> 47:26.111
We can't?
No!

47:26.177 --> 47:28.779
[SNORING]

47:32.984 --> 47:36.054
Okay, we get Devo.

47:36.121 --> 47:37.255
His brother was in Marines.

47:37.322 --> 47:39.624
He knows guns.

47:44.162 --> 47:47.465
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

47:47.532 --> 47:49.800
Hello.

47:49.867 --> 47:51.336
Devo, it's Nadja.

47:51.402 --> 47:52.303
Hey, Nadja.

47:52.370 --> 47:53.538
Are you alone?

47:53.604 --> 47:54.539
Yeah, why?

47:54.605 --> 47:55.606
Good.

47:55.673 --> 47:57.275
Devo, you know how
you feel about Rosalie?

47:57.342 --> 48:01.146
How you say how much
you like her?

48:01.212 --> 48:03.014
I love Rosalie.

48:03.081 --> 48:05.283
And how you would do
anything for her?

48:05.350 --> 48:06.517
Yes, anything.
Absolutely.

48:06.584 --> 48:10.755
Anything?
Yeah, anything. Why?

48:10.821 --> 48:13.291
You are a good boy,
very sweet.

48:13.358 --> 48:16.594
I want you to do
a little favor

48:16.661 --> 48:17.996
for Rosalie and me.

48:18.063 --> 48:19.931
You come to the house,
I'll tell you what it is.

48:19.998 --> 48:21.832
Okay.

48:32.843 --> 48:35.013
Wait a moment. Wait a minute.

48:35.080 --> 48:37.248
The bedspread is very
precious.

48:37.315 --> 48:39.284
Don't ruin it.

48:39.350 --> 48:41.519
Okay. On his back.

49:08.980 --> 49:10.081
You know what to do.

49:10.148 --> 49:11.849
Wait. Where
are you going?

49:11.916 --> 49:12.950
I can't watch.

49:13.018 --> 49:14.085
I can't
do this alone.

49:14.152 --> 49:15.420
He's my husband.

49:15.486 --> 49:17.255
Do you want him
dead or not?

49:17.322 --> 49:19.590
I want him dead,
but I don't want him hurt.

49:19.657 --> 49:20.958
He won't get hurt.
He won't.

49:21.026 --> 49:23.094
He's sound asleep.

49:23.161 --> 49:25.063
Yeah.

49:25.130 --> 49:26.897
We're keeping him
asleep forever.

49:26.964 --> 49:27.965
I can't watch.

49:28.033 --> 49:29.067
Rosalie!

49:41.279 --> 49:43.514
How long has it been?

49:43.581 --> 49:48.253
Pretty soon, Joey wakes up.
Then what?

49:52.457 --> 49:54.392
I can't do it.
I'm going to stop him.

49:54.459 --> 49:56.461
[GUNSHOT]

50:01.032 --> 50:02.100
Are you all right?

50:02.167 --> 50:03.101
Am I all right?

50:03.168 --> 50:04.502
Am I all--

50:04.569 --> 50:06.037
Why are you asking me
if I'm all right?

50:06.104 --> 50:07.905
He's the one
who got shot.

50:07.972 --> 50:09.140
You'd better sit down.

50:09.207 --> 50:11.076
No! I don't
want to sit down.

50:11.142 --> 50:13.111
What about Joey?

50:13.178 --> 50:14.412
Is he alive or dead?

50:14.479 --> 50:17.848
I don't know.

50:17.915 --> 50:19.884
Blood.

50:19.950 --> 50:21.552
No, tomato sauce.

50:21.619 --> 50:22.820
Tomato sauce?

50:22.887 --> 50:24.722
Did you shoot him
or not?

50:24.789 --> 50:26.624
I think so.

50:26.691 --> 50:28.626
What do you mean?
I heard a shot.

50:28.693 --> 50:32.197
I shot him, but I don't know
if I hit him.

50:32.263 --> 50:33.864
I mean, I turned my head away
at the last second.

50:33.931 --> 50:34.832
I'm sorry,

50:34.899 --> 50:36.167
but I couldn't
bear to watch.

50:36.234 --> 50:37.735
I thought you knew about guns.

50:37.802 --> 50:40.405
I never shot anyone before.

50:40.471 --> 50:42.473
Oh, don't worry.
I understand.

50:42.540 --> 50:44.209
There's a first time
for everything.

50:44.275 --> 50:46.377
I read about
a dental hygienist--

50:46.444 --> 50:48.413
Mama, never mind.

50:51.416 --> 50:52.783
Oh, wait.
There's some blood.

50:52.850 --> 50:56.053
Let me see.

50:56.121 --> 50:57.688
What is it?

50:57.755 --> 51:00.458
I think it's a bullet hole.
It's very small.

51:00.525 --> 51:04.129
A bullet hole?
Are you sure?

51:04.195 --> 51:05.396
Yes, I'm sure.

51:05.463 --> 51:06.831
Is he dead?

51:06.897 --> 51:09.367
Joey? Joey? Joey?

51:09.434 --> 51:11.569
Rosalie.
What?

51:12.970 --> 51:17.508
I don't feel so hot.
Got a little headache.

51:17.575 --> 51:20.911
My stomach don't feel
so hot neither.

51:20.978 --> 51:22.980
You got a virus, honey.

51:23.047 --> 51:25.150
That's all,
a virus.

51:25.216 --> 51:28.719
Virus? How can you tell?

51:28.786 --> 51:31.189
Dr. Lowe was here.

51:31.256 --> 51:32.657
He was?

51:32.723 --> 51:34.125
Yeah.

51:34.192 --> 51:35.560
I don't remember.

51:35.626 --> 51:39.164
Yeah, he was here,
and he gave you a shot.

51:39.230 --> 51:40.531
Ohh...

51:43.468 --> 51:46.737
Can I get
a glass of water?

51:46.804 --> 51:48.072
Rosalie?

51:48.139 --> 51:51.108
Maybe I take
a couple of aspirin too.

51:51.176 --> 51:52.210
Oh, okay.

51:58.949 --> 52:00.385
Whoa.

52:03.454 --> 52:04.922
NADJA: What are we
going to do?

52:06.691 --> 52:08.226
You're going to have
to shoot him again.

52:08.293 --> 52:09.727
No. I can't.

52:09.794 --> 52:12.062
I can't believe I did it
the first time.

52:12.129 --> 52:17.368
I can't believe
you let me do that.

52:17.435 --> 52:18.636
If you can't do it,

52:18.703 --> 52:19.704
you have to find
someone who can.

52:19.770 --> 52:21.506
I'll put up
the money.

52:21.572 --> 52:22.507
We need professionals.

52:22.573 --> 52:24.108
This has to be done
right away.

52:24.175 --> 52:25.376
Oh, you know
someone?

52:25.443 --> 52:29.079
I need to collect myself.

52:35.152 --> 52:38.556
All right, get a grip.

52:38.623 --> 52:41.559
Get your shit together.
Okay? Okay. Let's go.

52:45.530 --> 52:46.764
How much can we pay?

52:46.831 --> 52:51.168
As much
as we have to.

52:51.236 --> 52:52.370
Yeah, not too much,
though.

52:52.437 --> 52:54.405
You know,
try for discount.

53:17.295 --> 53:18.896
Is there
a Harlan James here?

53:18.963 --> 53:21.566
In the back, Devo.

53:33.043 --> 53:35.413
Hello, Harlan,
how's it going?

53:46.891 --> 53:49.327
Devo.

53:49.394 --> 53:51.629
What do you say?

53:58.803 --> 54:00.605
