01:12:20.937 --> 01:12:25.375
I know you do.

01:12:25.442 --> 01:12:28.978
You're my husband.

01:12:29.045 --> 01:12:31.047
Rosalie.

01:12:31.114 --> 01:12:33.683
Yeah?

01:12:38.855 --> 01:12:40.557
Oh, Joey, no.

01:12:40.624 --> 01:12:43.993
No, not now. Come on.

01:12:44.060 --> 01:12:46.963
Just lie quietly, okay?

01:12:58.575 --> 01:12:59.743
This is only 200.

01:12:59.809 --> 01:13:02.178
We was promised five.

01:13:02.245 --> 01:13:03.146
For killing him,
five.

01:13:03.212 --> 01:13:05.214
For wounding him,
two.

01:13:05.281 --> 01:13:08.051
Well, you wanted me
to shoot him, right?

01:13:08.117 --> 01:13:09.519
So I shot him.

01:13:09.586 --> 01:13:14.257
You woke him up.
What good is that?

01:13:24.734 --> 01:13:27.103
Okay.

01:13:37.847 --> 01:13:38.882
Next time we do this,

01:13:38.948 --> 01:13:42.051
we're going to get
paid in advance.

01:13:42.118 --> 01:13:43.653
If we keep shooting Joey,

01:13:43.720 --> 01:13:46.656
don't you think he might
get suspicious?

01:13:48.725 --> 01:13:50.694
Larry.

01:13:55.331 --> 01:13:57.300
Tell him
what you told me.

01:13:57.366 --> 01:13:58.468
I want to make a deal.

01:13:58.535 --> 01:14:00.504
Not that,
the other thing.

01:14:00.570 --> 01:14:02.171
There's not enough
heat in my cell.

01:14:02.238 --> 01:14:04.941
No, Harlan
and Marlon.

01:14:05.008 --> 01:14:06.576
Oh yeah.

01:14:06.643 --> 01:14:07.811
Harlan James
and his cousin Marlon.

01:14:07.877 --> 01:14:09.513
I heard they was paid
a lot of money

01:14:09.579 --> 01:14:12.649
to hit Joey Boca.

01:14:12.716 --> 01:14:15.985
Joey Boca? Why?

01:14:16.052 --> 01:14:17.654
I don't know.
That's what I heard, you know?

01:14:17.721 --> 01:14:19.355
Harlan and Marlon
was buying drinks for everyone

01:14:19.422 --> 01:14:20.857
and bragging on it.

01:14:20.924 --> 01:14:25.394
Said they shot the dude.
Said they got $5,000.

01:14:33.637 --> 01:14:37.173
[DOORBELL RINGS]

01:14:41.477 --> 01:14:43.246
It's kind of late.
Maybe they're asleep.

01:14:43.312 --> 01:14:45.448
[DOORBELL RINGS]

01:14:45.515 --> 01:14:46.683
I'd better answer.
I have to.

01:14:46.750 --> 01:14:50.253
No. No. Rosalie...

01:14:50.319 --> 01:14:53.557
Now, look, whatever happens,
let me do the talking.

01:14:53.623 --> 01:14:55.291
Mama, I don't want you
to say anything.

01:14:55.358 --> 01:14:56.325
What?

01:14:56.392 --> 01:14:57.827
You too, Devo.

01:14:57.894 --> 01:14:59.262
There's no sense everyone
getting in trouble.

01:14:59.328 --> 01:15:01.731
But I don't want you
to get in trouble.

01:15:01.798 --> 01:15:06.269
Anyway, Joey's not dead,
you know.

01:15:06.335 --> 01:15:09.573
All we did was put him to
sleep and wake him up a
few times.

01:15:09.639 --> 01:15:11.007
Mama, he has
two bullets in him.

01:15:11.074 --> 01:15:12.842
He could be dying.

01:15:12.909 --> 01:15:15.044
So how come
he wants meatballs?

01:15:17.614 --> 01:15:20.717
[RINGING]

01:15:22.586 --> 01:15:23.887
Evening, Rosalie.

01:15:23.953 --> 01:15:26.656
Is something wrong?

01:15:26.723 --> 01:15:27.824
May we come in?

01:15:27.891 --> 01:15:29.659
Oh, you mean now?

01:15:29.726 --> 01:15:31.260
We'd like to see Joey.

01:15:31.327 --> 01:15:32.796
Joey?

01:15:32.862 --> 01:15:34.598
Your husband. Joey.

01:15:34.664 --> 01:15:38.568
Oh, yeah, Joey. Oh, Joey.

01:15:38.635 --> 01:15:40.536
Uh, well, he's not feeling
well right now.

01:15:40.604 --> 01:15:43.239
Maybe you could come back
in a couple of days?

01:15:43.306 --> 01:15:44.473
Joey very sick.

01:15:44.540 --> 01:15:45.575
You come back
some other time.

01:15:45.642 --> 01:15:47.611
We'd like to see him tonight.

01:15:47.677 --> 01:15:49.145
Maybe tomorrow.

01:15:49.212 --> 01:15:53.416
Rosalie, if we have to,
we'll come back
with a warrant.

01:15:57.553 --> 01:15:59.555
Joey?

01:15:59.623 --> 01:16:03.893
Hey, Larry, how you doing?

01:16:05.995 --> 01:16:07.964
You all right?

01:16:08.031 --> 01:16:10.099
I got a little virus.

01:16:10.166 --> 01:16:11.267
A virus?

01:16:11.334 --> 01:16:13.703
Yes, some kind
of virus.

01:16:13.770 --> 01:16:16.372
I got a headache.

01:16:16.439 --> 01:16:18.441
You mind if I turn
on the light?

01:16:18.507 --> 01:16:20.944
Sure. Go ahead.

01:16:21.010 --> 01:16:23.747
I don't think you should.

01:16:23.813 --> 01:16:25.114
Just for a second.

01:16:25.181 --> 01:16:26.149
It doesn't work,
anyway.

01:16:26.215 --> 01:16:27.350
Oh.

01:16:34.090 --> 01:16:36.325
Get you nice
and comfortable.

01:16:38.361 --> 01:16:40.529
Excuse me, Rosalie.
Excuse me, please.

01:16:40.596 --> 01:16:44.634
Please, excuse me.
Thank you.

01:16:53.576 --> 01:16:54.610
Jesus.

01:16:54.678 --> 01:16:56.445
What?

01:16:56.512 --> 01:16:58.281
What the hell's going on here?

01:16:58.347 --> 01:17:00.950
He's been shot in the head.

01:17:01.017 --> 01:17:03.653
Really?
What?

01:17:03.720 --> 01:17:05.822
No wonder
he has headache.

01:17:05.889 --> 01:17:08.825
Headache?
He's got a bullet in him.

01:17:08.892 --> 01:17:12.061
Carlos, get an ambulance
over here right away.

01:17:12.128 --> 01:17:14.831
Devo!

01:17:14.898 --> 01:17:17.500
I was going to get a Band-Aid
for Joey.

01:17:19.635 --> 01:17:21.537
Yeah, this is Detective
Carlos Wiley.

01:17:21.604 --> 01:17:24.107
I'm at 424 North C,
as in "Charlie."

01:17:24.173 --> 01:17:27.410
We didn't do it.
I swear to God we didn't.

01:17:27.476 --> 01:17:30.179
We found him
outside on the lawn.

01:17:30.246 --> 01:17:31.815
Yeah.
He was lying there.

01:17:31.881 --> 01:17:34.818
Someone had shot him
and thrown him on the lawn.

01:17:34.884 --> 01:17:35.952
It was a mess.

01:17:36.019 --> 01:17:37.520
It was terrible,
so we...

01:17:37.586 --> 01:17:39.856
we brought him inside
and we put him in bed.

01:17:39.923 --> 01:17:40.990
Yeah, like you see.

01:17:41.057 --> 01:17:42.258
And it must have been
the Mafia.

01:17:42.325 --> 01:17:43.326
Mafia?

01:17:43.392 --> 01:17:45.194
The Mafia.

01:17:45.261 --> 01:17:46.896
Yeah, Joey was Italian.

01:17:46.963 --> 01:17:48.164
He is Italian.

01:17:48.231 --> 01:17:51.534
Rosalie, why didn't you take
him to the hospital?

01:17:51.600 --> 01:17:52.668
He didn't want to go.

01:17:52.736 --> 01:17:54.137
He wasn't
feeling up to it.

01:17:54.203 --> 01:17:56.873
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

01:17:56.940 --> 01:18:02.545
Joey, you didn't want
to go to the hospital?

01:18:02.611 --> 01:18:05.314
No. Why,
for a virus?

01:18:05.381 --> 01:18:07.917
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

01:18:11.955 --> 01:18:14.623
[**]

01:18:15.959 --> 01:18:17.560
Rosalie. Don't tell Rosalie.

01:18:43.019 --> 01:18:44.220
How many bottles
of pills

01:18:44.287 --> 01:18:45.588
did you give him?

01:18:45.654 --> 01:18:49.258
I gave him two bottles.
One, two.

01:18:49.325 --> 01:18:53.897
Harlan and Marlon say
Devo shot him the first time.

01:18:53.963 --> 01:18:55.198
Is that right?

01:18:55.264 --> 01:18:57.033
Devo wouldn't even
have been there

01:18:57.100 --> 01:18:57.967
if it wasn't for me.

01:18:58.034 --> 01:18:59.969
How do you mean?

01:19:00.036 --> 01:19:04.007
I wanted to kill Joey.
Devo had nothing to
do with it.

01:19:04.073 --> 01:19:06.209
Did Devo shoot him or not?

01:19:06.275 --> 01:19:07.476
What does Devo say?

01:19:07.543 --> 01:19:08.711
Never mind him.
What do you say?

01:19:08.778 --> 01:19:11.547
It wasn't Devo. It was me.

01:19:11.614 --> 01:19:15.751
I shot him the first time,
and then...

01:19:15.819 --> 01:19:18.454
Who shot him? Let me see.
It was Marlon.

01:19:18.521 --> 01:19:20.689
No, no. Harlan. Harlan.

01:19:20.756 --> 01:19:22.725
Are you sure?

01:19:22.792 --> 01:19:26.095
Yeah, I'm sure.
Why? Who do you think
shot him?

01:19:26.162 --> 01:19:27.263
What about your mother?

01:19:27.330 --> 01:19:30.266
She had nothing to do with it.
Nothing.

01:19:30.333 --> 01:19:33.136
Yes, I shoot him. Yes.

01:19:33.202 --> 01:19:36.405
You know why?
He is no-good son of a bitch.

01:19:36.472 --> 01:19:37.974
Who gave him the pills?

01:19:38.041 --> 01:19:39.608
I did.
What do you think?

01:19:39.675 --> 01:19:40.944
First I give him
sleeping pills,

01:19:41.010 --> 01:19:42.011
then I shoot him.

01:19:42.078 --> 01:19:43.813
You want me to confess?

01:19:43.880 --> 01:19:45.581
Give me piece of paper.
I confess.

01:19:45.648 --> 01:19:47.316
What about Rosalie?

01:19:47.383 --> 01:19:49.252
Rosalie? She does nothing.

01:19:49.318 --> 01:19:50.686
No, I do everything.

01:19:50.753 --> 01:19:54.057
I give him pills,
I shoot him, everything.

01:19:54.123 --> 01:19:56.659
And while you were doing this,
what was your daughter doing?

01:19:56.725 --> 01:20:01.564
She was begging me to stop.

01:20:01.630 --> 01:20:05.701
But I do it anyway,
and you know why?

01:20:05.768 --> 01:20:09.472
I am her mother.
I do what I like.

01:20:09.538 --> 01:20:11.975
I thought Devo shot him
the first time.

01:20:12.041 --> 01:20:13.877
Devo?

01:20:13.943 --> 01:20:16.145
Oh, no.
You must be joking.

01:20:16.212 --> 01:20:17.613
No, Devo's very nice boy.

01:20:17.680 --> 01:20:20.216
He wouldn't shoot
nobody.

01:20:20.283 --> 01:20:21.650
I don't understand

01:20:21.717 --> 01:20:23.752
why you're trying
to blame it on Rosalie.

01:20:23.819 --> 01:20:25.554
Maybe I did it.

01:20:25.621 --> 01:20:27.123
Maybe I'm glad
I did it.

01:20:27.190 --> 01:20:28.992
Are you saying
you did it?

01:20:29.058 --> 01:20:30.159
No, he's not
saying that.

01:20:30.226 --> 01:20:31.460
What's he saying?

01:20:31.527 --> 01:20:36.232
He's not saying
anything.

01:20:36.299 --> 01:20:38.201
I know how to fire a gun.

01:20:38.267 --> 01:20:40.236
My brother was in
the National Guard.

01:20:40.303 --> 01:20:41.871
So what are you
saying?

01:20:41.938 --> 01:20:48.912
He's saying that his brother
is a patriotic American.

01:20:57.286 --> 01:20:59.222
Ms. Boca, was it
a crime of passion?

01:20:59.288 --> 01:21:02.358
Look at all these people.

01:21:02.425 --> 01:21:04.593
Rosalie, it's me, Tony.
What can you tell me?

01:21:04.660 --> 01:21:06.195
Mama, remember, you had
nothing to do with it.

01:21:06.262 --> 01:21:08.264
Tonight
I bet you anything

01:21:08.331 --> 01:21:10.633
we'll be on TV,
you and me.

01:21:10.699 --> 01:21:12.168
Can you imagine?

01:21:12.235 --> 01:21:14.904
Rosalie, can you
give us a statement?

01:21:19.342 --> 01:21:21.744
Devo. Devo, what
can you tell us?

01:21:21.810 --> 01:21:23.079
What happened?

01:21:23.146 --> 01:21:24.347
Is it true that
the Mafia involved?

01:21:24.413 --> 01:21:25.381
I have nothing to say
at this time.

01:21:25.448 --> 01:21:26.782
No comment.

01:21:26.849 --> 01:21:28.551
What about you,
sir?

01:21:28.617 --> 01:21:30.319
Get the fuck away from me.

01:21:30.386 --> 01:21:32.288
What about Joey?
Is he dead, or what?

01:21:32.355 --> 01:21:34.857
Who's Joey?

01:21:34.924 --> 01:21:37.460
You know, the guy.
The guy.

01:21:37.526 --> 01:21:39.328
Oh, yeah, the guy.

01:21:39.395 --> 01:21:40.263
Fuck.

01:21:40.329 --> 01:21:41.497
He's still alive.

01:21:41.564 --> 01:21:42.898
Why? What do you
know about it?

01:21:42.966 --> 01:21:46.169
Oh, nothing.

01:21:58.114 --> 01:22:00.183
Rosalie...

01:22:17.500 --> 01:22:18.501
Lacey.

01:22:18.567 --> 01:22:20.169
How you doing?

01:22:20.236 --> 01:22:22.205
Hi, Joey. How do you feel?

01:22:27.610 --> 01:22:30.579
You should see all
the reporters outside.

01:22:30.646 --> 01:22:33.382
You're going to be
so famous.

01:22:33.449 --> 01:22:34.783
I even heard
People magazine

01:22:34.850 --> 01:22:36.052
was going to interview you.

01:22:36.119 --> 01:22:36.952
Lacey, you shouldn't
be here now.

01:22:37.020 --> 01:22:38.554
It's not right.

01:22:38.621 --> 01:22:41.924
But the doctor said you're
going to be out in a week.

01:22:41.991 --> 01:22:47.130
Listen, baby...

01:22:47.196 --> 01:22:50.266
when somebody
shoot you in the head...

01:22:50.333 --> 01:22:52.135
it makes you think.

01:22:52.201 --> 01:22:54.303
I've been doing
a lot of thinking lately,

01:22:54.370 --> 01:22:57.540
a whole lot, and...

01:22:57.606 --> 01:22:58.841
I can't mess around anymore.

01:22:58.907 --> 01:23:00.309
I've got to be, you know,
a good husband.

01:23:00.376 --> 01:23:01.977
From now on, I've got to take
my marriage

01:23:02.045 --> 01:23:02.945
a little more serious.

01:23:03.012 --> 01:23:04.113
You know what I mean?

01:23:04.180 --> 01:23:06.449
Joey, what are you saying?

01:23:06.515 --> 01:23:09.152
She shot you. Twice.

01:23:09.218 --> 01:23:10.719
No, no, no, no, no, no.

01:23:10.786 --> 01:23:14.157
She never shot me herself,
per se.

01:23:14.223 --> 01:23:17.926
So what about us?

01:23:17.993 --> 01:23:22.431
That's what I'm trying
to tell you.

01:23:22.498 --> 01:23:26.902
That's all over now.

01:23:26.969 --> 01:23:29.938
I always told you
I loved my wife.

01:23:33.476 --> 01:23:35.544
Joey, who is this woman?

01:23:38.147 --> 01:23:41.384
Mama, this is Lacey.

01:23:41.450 --> 01:23:42.418
She's a friend of mine.

01:23:42.485 --> 01:23:45.454
My Joey has to get his rest.

01:23:45.521 --> 01:23:47.123
You shouldn't be here now.

01:23:47.190 --> 01:23:48.124
I was just leaving.

01:23:48.191 --> 01:23:50.159
Good. Just leave.

01:23:50.226 --> 01:23:51.627
You don't belong here anyway.

01:23:51.694 --> 01:23:53.296
You're not his wife.

01:23:56.265 --> 01:23:58.734
I'll see you
later, Joey.

01:24:15.251 --> 01:24:17.753
How are you feeling today?

01:24:17.820 --> 01:24:24.026
Okay, Mama, better.

01:24:24.093 --> 01:24:26.929
I spoke to Rosalie
this morning.

01:24:26.995 --> 01:24:30.966
You did? What
did she tell you?

01:24:31.033 --> 01:24:34.270
What did she tell me?

01:24:34.337 --> 01:24:37.506
She told me the truth.

01:24:37.573 --> 01:24:40.376
What's the matter
with you, you big shot?

01:24:40.443 --> 01:24:41.344
Cheating on your wife.

01:24:41.410 --> 01:24:43.011
Ai, Mama!

01:24:43.078 --> 01:24:47.250
Please, I got
a bullet in my head.

01:24:47.316 --> 01:24:49.118
You should have
two bullets in your head.

01:24:49.185 --> 01:24:50.453
Three bullets!
Four bullets!

01:24:50.519 --> 01:24:53.222
Ai! Mama, please,
I'm so sorry.

01:24:53.289 --> 01:24:54.457
What can I say?

01:24:56.592 --> 01:25:01.164
You no tell me
you're sorry.

01:25:01.230 --> 01:25:02.465
No.
No.

01:25:02.531 --> 01:25:06.135
You tell Rosalie.

01:25:06.202 --> 01:25:08.604
Oh, si, good idea.
Sure, yeah.

01:25:08.671 --> 01:25:12.275
Otherwise, I give you
such a beating...

01:25:12.341 --> 01:25:14.810
Okay.

01:25:14.877 --> 01:25:19.215
Mama, that's
a good idea.

01:25:21.317 --> 01:25:23.586
Oh, no.

01:25:23.652 --> 01:25:26.589
Mama...

01:25:33.429 --> 01:25:35.398
Ai!

01:25:35.464 --> 01:25:37.366
[SOBBING]

01:25:37.433 --> 01:25:41.604
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

01:25:46.309 --> 01:25:47.910
How can you
bail her out?

01:25:47.976 --> 01:25:49.044
Don't you see
what that means?

01:25:49.111 --> 01:25:52.047
It means she can come home.

01:25:52.114 --> 01:25:53.616
In the hospital,

01:25:53.682 --> 01:25:55.117
you said
you'd prosecute.

01:25:55.184 --> 01:25:57.653
I know, Larry.
I changed my mind.

01:25:57.720 --> 01:25:59.021
I'm sorry.

01:25:59.087 --> 01:26:02.558
I learned a lot
in the last few weeks.

01:26:02.625 --> 01:26:04.527
You wouldn't have
revenge on your mind,

01:26:04.593 --> 01:26:05.528
would you, Joey?

01:26:05.594 --> 01:26:08.197
She's my wife.

01:26:08.264 --> 01:26:10.833
I want to bring her home.

01:26:10.899 --> 01:26:11.934
I love her.

01:26:12.000 --> 01:26:13.135
You understand?

01:26:13.202 --> 01:26:15.170
She shouldn't be in prison.

01:26:15.238 --> 01:26:17.373
She's the mother of
my children.

01:26:19.141 --> 01:26:20.676
Maybe she had plenty
of good reasons

01:26:20.743 --> 01:26:22.911
for trying to kill me.

01:26:22.978 --> 01:26:24.213
You ever think
of that?

01:26:24.280 --> 01:26:26.982
Joe, suppose she tries again.

01:26:27.049 --> 01:26:28.050
She could, you know.

01:26:28.116 --> 01:26:31.887
Yeah, she could.

01:26:31.954 --> 01:26:34.223
You know Rosalie.

01:26:34.290 --> 01:26:40.863
When she's in love,
she's a complete maniac.

01:26:49.204 --> 01:26:51.574
Don't get your dress wet
for Mommy.

01:26:51.640 --> 01:26:54.310
I won't.

01:27:03.452 --> 01:27:06.322
[BELL RINGING]

01:27:06.389 --> 01:27:08.424
[BUZZ]

01:27:13.061 --> 01:27:14.630
Hey, Devo!

01:27:17.566 --> 01:27:18.834
Devo!

01:27:18.901 --> 01:27:20.168
How are you?

01:27:20.235 --> 01:27:22.971
Devo?

01:27:32.047 --> 01:27:34.717
Wait, Marlon...

01:27:34.783 --> 01:27:36.585
look who's here.

01:27:36.652 --> 01:27:38.020
Hey, wow.

01:27:38.086 --> 01:27:39.822
How you doing?

01:27:39.888 --> 01:27:41.089
I'm okay.

01:27:41.156 --> 01:27:43.258
Who is this?

01:27:46.128 --> 01:27:47.763
This is Joey.

01:27:47.830 --> 01:27:48.831
Joey?

01:27:48.897 --> 01:27:51.600
You know, the guy.

01:27:51.667 --> 01:27:54.169
The guy.

01:27:54.236 --> 01:27:59.642
Oh. Wow. Joey.

01:28:00.943 --> 01:28:02.811
You bailed us out.

01:28:02.878 --> 01:28:04.813
Yeah, I bail out
everybody.

01:28:04.880 --> 01:28:06.382
I want to
make a new start,

01:28:06.449 --> 01:28:07.783
wipe the slate clean.

01:28:07.850 --> 01:28:10.486
I hear they may charge us
with attempted murder.

01:28:10.553 --> 01:28:12.821
No, no, no. I'm not
going to prosecute.

01:28:12.888 --> 01:28:14.357
See, if I prosecute you,

01:28:14.423 --> 01:28:16.325
they're going to put
Rosalie in jail too.

01:28:16.392 --> 01:28:17.626
I don't want that.

01:28:17.693 --> 01:28:19.227
No, without me,
they got no case.

01:28:19.294 --> 01:28:20.329
Don't worry.

01:28:20.396 --> 01:28:22.865
Hey, you know,
what happened,

01:28:22.931 --> 01:28:25.468
it wasn't personal
or anything.

01:28:25.534 --> 01:28:26.869
Yeah.

01:28:26.935 --> 01:28:29.438
Right. I mean...

01:28:29.505 --> 01:28:31.374
we didn't even know you
or anything.

01:28:31.440 --> 01:28:33.642
Yeah, we weren't friends
or anything,

01:28:33.709 --> 01:28:35.043
like now.

01:28:35.110 --> 01:28:40.549
No. No. It wasn't
the best way to meet.

01:28:40.616 --> 01:28:43.452
We'd better
get out of here,

01:28:43.519 --> 01:28:46.188
you know, before they
change their mind.

01:28:46.254 --> 01:28:49.091
Yeah. Right.

01:28:49.157 --> 01:28:52.060
So long, Joey.

01:28:52.127 --> 01:28:53.295
I guess
we'll see you around.

01:28:53.362 --> 01:28:55.798
Okay.

01:29:01.837 --> 01:29:03.672
Oh, what a nice guy.

01:29:03.739 --> 01:29:04.773
Yeah.

01:29:04.840 --> 01:29:07.142
Who's Rosalie?

01:29:07.209 --> 01:29:08.877
[CRASH]

01:29:12.981 --> 01:29:17.019
Joey, I'm really,
really sorry

01:29:17.085 --> 01:29:18.320
about what happened.

01:29:22.625 --> 01:29:25.728
You tried to tell me
a long time ago, Devo.

01:29:25.794 --> 01:29:28.230
I should have
listened to you.

01:29:28.296 --> 01:29:29.732
I wasn't treating
Rosalie right.

01:29:29.798 --> 01:29:31.767
Rosalie is
a wonderful lady.

01:29:31.834 --> 01:29:34.603
I know. I'm going to
make it up to her.

01:29:34.670 --> 01:29:35.538
Good.

01:29:35.604 --> 01:29:37.540
Thanks for
bailing me out.

01:29:37.606 --> 01:29:38.974
Sure, sure.

01:29:39.041 --> 01:29:41.176
Just no more shooting me
in the head, okay?

01:29:41.243 --> 01:29:44.212
Why not? It seems
to have helped.

01:29:44.279 --> 01:29:46.515
It's the truth.

01:29:46.582 --> 01:29:50.786
I got a bullet in my head,
I never felt better.

01:29:51.820 --> 01:29:54.690
[BELL RINGING]

01:29:54.757 --> 01:29:57.926
[BUZZ]

01:29:57.993 --> 01:29:59.528
Hi, Mom.

01:30:00.496 --> 01:30:02.765
Oh, my babies!

01:30:02.831 --> 01:30:06.902
Oh, Dominic,
Dominic.

01:30:06.969 --> 01:30:10.973
Don't worry,
we're safe.

01:30:11.039 --> 01:30:12.675
Don't worry.

01:30:19.548 --> 01:30:20.883
So, what do you want?

01:30:20.949 --> 01:30:26.288
I'm sorry I treat
your daughter so bad.

01:30:26.354 --> 01:30:29.525
I broke my marriage vows...

01:30:29.592 --> 01:30:32.260
but I don't break nothing
ever again, I swear.

01:30:32.327 --> 01:30:36.031
And this is for me,
this candy?

01:30:36.098 --> 01:30:37.933
Well, I...

01:30:38.000 --> 01:30:39.568
Yeah, thank you.

01:30:39.635 --> 01:30:40.736
You're very good boy.

01:30:40.803 --> 01:30:44.272
Yeah, you know,
I liked you once.

01:30:44.339 --> 01:30:47.375
Maybe I like you again...

01:30:47.442 --> 01:30:50.513
except chocolate
is not my favorite.

01:30:50.579 --> 01:30:52.815
I like hard candy.

01:30:52.881 --> 01:30:54.149
Well, I'll remember--

01:30:54.216 --> 01:30:56.852
No, no, no, no.
I keep this for now.

01:30:58.420 --> 01:30:59.955
ROSALIE: Great. I can't
wait to get home.

01:31:00.022 --> 01:31:01.890
Dominic. Dominic, come.

01:31:01.957 --> 01:31:03.726
You come with me.

01:31:03.792 --> 01:31:06.829
Come with me, I give you
some of my candy.

01:31:09.364 --> 01:31:12.200
We go find Devo.
Come.

01:31:26.281 --> 01:31:27.950
What's this?

01:31:28.016 --> 01:31:29.518
What are you
giving me flowers for?

01:31:35.123 --> 01:31:36.625
I want you
to marry me again.

01:31:36.692 --> 01:31:37.660
What?

01:31:37.726 --> 01:31:41.163
A new marriage, new life.

01:31:41.229 --> 01:31:44.366
We have big ceremony.

01:31:48.436 --> 01:31:49.805
You think I'm going to
make the same mistake?

01:31:49.872 --> 01:31:51.239
We're not even divorced yet.

01:31:51.306 --> 01:31:53.241
How can you marry me again?

01:31:53.308 --> 01:31:54.710
Rosie! Rosie!

01:31:57.846 --> 01:32:00.683
Come here, please.

01:32:00.749 --> 01:32:04.119
I love you.
I bailed you out.

01:32:04.186 --> 01:32:06.488
Don't do this
to me again, Joey.

01:32:06.555 --> 01:32:08.591
I tried to kill you.

01:32:08.657 --> 01:32:11.026
No.
You saved my life.

01:32:11.093 --> 01:32:12.427
What?

01:32:12.494 --> 01:32:14.362
Those sleeping pills
you gave me,

01:32:14.429 --> 01:32:16.131
they slowed down
my bleeding.

01:32:16.198 --> 01:32:17.132
It's what kept me alive.

01:32:17.199 --> 01:32:18.300
The doctor told me.

01:32:18.366 --> 01:32:19.568
Son of bitch,

01:32:19.635 --> 01:32:21.303
you cheated on me
all these years.

01:32:21.369 --> 01:32:22.771
Why should I trust you now?

01:32:22.838 --> 01:32:25.440
Because I'm changed.
I'm a new man.

01:32:25.507 --> 01:32:27.275
Why? Why now
all of a sudden?

01:32:27.342 --> 01:32:29.477
Because you shot me.

01:32:29.544 --> 01:32:32.080
What?

01:32:32.147 --> 01:32:35.350
Oh, Rosie, when I woke up
in that hospital

01:32:35.417 --> 01:32:37.552
and I found out
what happened,

01:32:37.620 --> 01:32:39.021
I said to myself,

01:32:39.087 --> 01:32:42.625
"My God, this woman,
she loves me to death."

01:32:42.691 --> 01:32:46.929
She loves me so much
she'd rather kill me

01:32:46.995 --> 01:32:49.331
than see me
with another woman.

01:32:49.397 --> 01:32:50.966
She's ready to go
to prison for me,

01:32:51.033 --> 01:32:52.668
she loves me so much.

01:32:52.735 --> 01:32:54.837
Oh, baby.

01:32:54.903 --> 01:32:58.106
That's all I needed,
just to feel your passion,

01:32:58.173 --> 01:33:01.944
to know you still love me
like a man...

01:33:02.010 --> 01:33:06.949
not like a husband,
like a man.

01:33:08.050 --> 01:33:09.251
You are my husband.

01:33:09.317 --> 01:33:10.653
You should be proud of it.

01:33:10.719 --> 01:33:13.455
I'm your wife.
I was always proud of it.

01:33:13.521 --> 01:33:14.890
Okay, you're right.

01:33:14.957 --> 01:33:16.792
I am your husband.

01:33:16.859 --> 01:33:18.426
I'll be proud too.

01:33:18.493 --> 01:33:21.463
I'll never cheat on you
again. Never.

01:33:21.529 --> 01:33:23.966
Oh, Rosie, I love you.

01:33:24.032 --> 01:33:25.033
Be my wife again.

01:33:25.100 --> 01:33:26.902
Oh, you're crazy.

01:33:26.969 --> 01:33:28.536
Don't you see?

01:33:28.603 --> 01:33:29.805
It's our destiny.

01:33:29.872 --> 01:33:31.339
We're doomed to be together.

01:33:31.406 --> 01:33:32.908
Like Romeo and Juliet.

01:33:32.975 --> 01:33:35.210
And I'll always
be faithful to you.

01:33:35.277 --> 01:33:36.578
Like Romeo and Juliet.

01:33:36.645 --> 01:33:38.546
Whatever.

01:33:51.426 --> 01:33:53.428
You think Joey can be
faithful to her?

01:33:53.495 --> 01:33:55.030
Anything is possible.

01:33:55.097 --> 01:33:56.999
He gave me
a box of candy.

01:33:57.065 --> 01:33:59.067
[MOANING]

01:33:59.134 --> 01:34:01.269
What if he isn't?

01:34:01.336 --> 01:34:03.405
We shoot him again.

01:34:06.174 --> 01:34:09.444
Just kidding.
